definitions.definition: Not likely ; improbable; not to be reasonably expected.
examples: It is pretty unlikely that you'll win, but I will pray that at least you do well .
In the highly unlikely event of landing in water, lifejackets are stored under the seat.

definitions.definition: Not holding out a prospect of success; likely to fail; unpromising.

main_definition: Not likely ; improbable; not to be reasonably expected.
secondary_definitions: Not holding out a prospect of success; likely to fail; unpromising.
